						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, Chōḷēśvara shrine, Agastyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 13: 984 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the gift of an image of Gaṇapati with <hi rend="italic">pīṭha</hi> and <hi rend="italic">prabhā</hi> for the purpose of procession and also a gold flower for the same deity for the temple of Mahādēva at Avanigandharva-Īśvaragṛiham, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadānam</hi> in Kuṉṟa-kūṟṟam by Kaṇḍaṉ Dēvaḍi of Nāvalūr, the <hi rend="italic">śrīkāriyam</hi> official, on the orders of the chief Aḍigaḷ Paḻuvēṭṭaraiyaṉ Kaṇḍaṉ Sundaraśōḻaṉ.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 327. </p>						

						</summary>
